Absolutely lovely family asked me to do a dining room refresh for them. Piece by piece we pulled it together. Added new lights to enhance the space, drapes to add softness to the walls, well scaled and balanced furniture to fill the big open space and hand picked, curated and thoughtful accessories to finish up this moody space. We are missing a small few accents and then this dining room will be ready to embrace the beginning of many cozy meals with friends and family. Since you tend to like my iPhone reels a bit more now, so here it is until we take some good professional photos. 

Happy Friday sweet people 🤍

Same view just after a short one year of full gut renovation of this living room. When I first walked into this home, the first thing I noticed was this off centered fireplace and a wall full of potential. With my clients trust, we took down the entire thing and created a beautiful focal point for this room with a brand new marble fireplace surround and the beautiful new built ins. Symmetry in design is something I love to achieve whenever possible. I love how this room transformed into a cozy casual space for my clients to share and enjoy with their family and friends. I will share more posts on this soon. Absolutely love the gorgeous photos @sumairaamberphoto took of the space and can’t wait to share more. 

P.S “A gentle reminder to please donate whatever you can in your capacity to help people of #turkeyearthquake and #syriaearthquake. We cannot possibly fathom anything those innocent souls are going through. And be grateful for the homes you get to live in no matter how they are designed or decorated. Life is bigger than that.”

Happy Friday 🤗

I have been hiding a project for way too long. And not sure how I managed keeping it completely off the grid till now. But now it’s time to share it. It’s my first ever commercial project. I was reached out by the owner of @naanncurry restaurant in Issaquah Wa for a remodel and redesign of their dine in area. I was reluctant and hesitant to be honest. Because I was not sure if it was the niche I want myself involved in. Plus all the legalities that come with working on a hospitality project. But opportunities don’t knock twice. I wanted to challenge myself and it has been such an amazing and rewarding experience to work on a restaurant that shares my roots, culture and values. They have been in business for a decade and we wanted to take that inheritance for the love and passion of good quality food to the next level. 

My vision for the space was that it should feel like a big hug when someone walks in and feel welcomed and have this feeling of a cozy warm space to dine in. It should not only reflect the roots and authenticity of what Pakistan is all about but also that it represents strong Pakistani American Muslims in various fields of design, art and food industry. I am so proud of this project and can’t wait to share photos taken by my talented friends @sumairaamberphoto and @nataliyakhan

Most of the beautiful art we got curated and commissioned thoughtfully by the talented @sobiasart
I also sourced a lot of art directly from artists in Pakistan to name a few @mansab_art, @shuzakart @tahirbilal.ummi. All the frames are vintage and sourced at different vintage antique shops around Seattle area. That took me the longest. New frames wouldn’t have done justice to that old, lived in feel I was going for. And love how that adds character and patina to all the art pieces here. 

What a great collaborative project and love what we were able to achieve here. If you are local to Seattle area, do yourself a favor and book a table here asap. Don’t forget to tag me while you are there. I can’t wait for you to experience it :-) 

Also a big shout out to my contractor @prestige.stone.llc for pulling it off and dealing with my endless calls, messages and demands :-)

Happy Saturday friends 🤍

Some before and after photos on the projects I get the opportunity to work on literally make me skip a beat. I love how you can look back and see where you started and how much is possible to achieve in our homes. It’s true when they say “ kitchen is the heart of a home”. I am just simply excited for my clients to enjoy this space after a long excruciating renovation. But it was all so worth it. 

We went with custom oak wood cabinets everywhere, the new pantry wall has ample amount of pull out drawers for storage and convenience. We rearranged the layout and moved the stove under a large scale window to enjoy the beautiful view. Built in espresso machine is probably my favorite element. The hidden appliance garage next to the stove make it easy for the kitchen to look beautiful and clean always but is also practical when in use. We selected only the finest materials here and the stunning marble really sets the tone for the entire space. I hope you love it as much as I do.

As heavy as my heart is right now, the feeling of a safe home and having my loved ones close by is the only thing that’s bringing some peace to my restless heart. For so many, home is just a memory. And that’s hard to process!!

Received this gorgeous rug from @loloirugs. This is the Rocky ROC-01 Ivory / Silver Area Rug from their third collaboration with @amberinteriors rocky collection. The rocky collection is Meticulously hand-tufted and features undyed wool that creates beautiful color variation and texture for a warm, inviting ambiance that complements a variety of design styles. Rocky is also GoodWeave-Certified that ensures ethical production and the support of weavers’ communities. I loved styling it in my living room and love how it adds subtle softness and texture to my space and also feel great.
Also received two gorgeous pillows, and they are perfect addition to my pillow collection. Will share the link in my story. Hope you enjoy the new #amberlewisxloloi collection as much as I do.

Just wanted to take a moment to appreciate good and real connections with like minded genuine people. I have recently got reached out by @katiehintzzambrano who is an amazing soul from @mothermag and she invited me to two of the most beautifully hosted events. Loved being around amazing and talented women from all walks of life. This particular event was hosted in collaboration with @caclosets @californiaclosetsseattle at this sweet venue @cafefloraveg 

We talked about what home means to us, a topic that seems more pressing than ever, given the state of the world. Answers included “safety,” “ritual,” “restoration,” “tradition,” “privilege,” “freedom,” “grandma’s house,” “my husband and cat,” “rest,” and so forth. 

Loved the goodies given out by the courtesy of some of the best small businesses including:

@heathceramics @idlewildfloral @wundergroundcoffee (the best I have had so far)
@belovedbyv (all what my aching body needed)
@mooreaseal art work (cutest)
And magazines from @caclosets 

I don’t take inner beauty for granted and absolutely love how @_karamercer captured the essence of this special soulful event 🥰

If this thanksgiving means anything to me right now, it’s being thankful to the beautiful souls who cultivate sense of a safe community to voice our deepest fears about the world we live in. 

Have a good one!
~Ayesha

I have installed a full 2900sqft home that my clients purchased as a vacation rental in Lake Chelan.
